# harness-strict-mode.patch — verification strict mode + coverage accounting (ROI-TOP-50 item 1)
#
# Apply with `git apply -p1` (or `patch -p1`) from the REPOSITORY ROOT — unlike the src/-relative
# feature patches, this one also touches the fork-only verification/ and scripts/ trees, which do not
# exist in stock VeraCrypt 1.26.29.
#
# What it does:
#   * verification/build_and_verify.sh: adds a coverage line ("N/48 steps verified, M skipped") on
#     every run, and a --strict / VC_STRICT=1 mode that makes ANY skipped step exit non-zero, so a
#     partially-covered run can no longer report all-green. Also FIXES the two steps that were
#     silently skipping (masking real harness link defects):
#       - step 6 (KeyScrub): build the HKF path so the REAL HKFScrubActiveConfig is exercised;
#       - step 9 (Keyslots lifecycle): add the missing AfSplit.o to the link line.
#     Adds a VC_SELFTEST_FORCE_SKIP negative control that exercises --strict cheaply.
#   * scripts/verify.sh: forwards args ("$@") so `scripts/verify.sh --strict` reaches the suite.
#   * src/Common/HardwareKeyFactor.c: tightens the HKFScrubActiveConfig guard to
#     `VC_ENABLE_KEYSCRUB && VC_ENABLE_HKF`, making it the exact complement of the KeyScrub.c stub
#     (`VC_ENABLE_KEYSCRUB && !VC_ENABLE_HKF`). Without this, a KEYSCRUB-on/HKF-off build defined the
#     symbol twice (link error). The src/ hunk builds on this fork's HardwareKeyFactor series.
#
# Verified: `scripts/verify.sh --strict` -> exit 0, "48/48 steps verified, 0 skipped".
#
diff --git a/scripts/verify.sh b/scripts/verify.sh
